Consider two OCaml implementations of Fibonacci:<br><pre><code>let rec fib1 n =
  if n &lt;= 1 then n
  else fib1 (n-1) + fib1 (n-2)

let fib2 n =
  let rec go a b n =
    if n = 0 then a
    else go b (a+b) (n-1)
  in go 0 1 n</code></pre><br>Give the time complexity of each. Explain why <code>fib1</code> is exponential by describing the computation tree. What optimisation does <code>fib2</code> use?
